%% Diagram: Spanner commit wait turns clock uncertainty into external consistency
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant TT as TrueTime
    participant Co as Coordinator
    participant P as Participants

    Co->>P: prepare
    P-->>Co: prepare ts

    Co->>TT: TT.now()
    TT-->>Co: [earliest, latest]
    Co->>Co: pick s = max(latest,\nprepare ts, prev commit + 1)

    note over Co,TT: Commit wait —\nblock until earliest > s\n(typically 1–7 ms)
    Co->>TT: TT.now()
    TT-->>Co: earliest <= s
    Co->>TT: TT.now()
    TT-->>Co: earliest > s

    Co->>P: COMMIT at s
    note over Co,P: Any later real-time tx\ngets a timestamp > s.\nReal-time order preserved.
